                            <comment id="17001276" author="bdeggleston" created="Fri, 20 Dec 2019 22:53:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/bdeggleston/cassandra/tree/15463-4.0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;4.0&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://circleci.com/workflow-run/f1845b60-c8be-41d1-8cea-b03f8a8bc064&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;circle&lt;/a&gt;\&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Added a flag to ant, and reworked a test. The failing repair test is also failing on trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17009227" author="dcapwell" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2020 23:19:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Started testing this now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org.apache.cassandra.distributed.test.MessageForwardingTest#mutationsForwardedToAllReplicasTest is failing since the logic in the stream doesn&apos;t seem to be executing anymore. &#160;In speaking with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=bdeggleston&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;bdeggleston&quot;&gt;bdeggleston&lt;/a&gt;&#160;seems that streams is able to avoid calling the map logic to compute count, so map gets skipped (which causes the test to fail).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have yet to replicate the issue that the build change is trying to solve&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17009265" author="dcapwell" created="Tue, 7 Jan 2020 00:52:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM. &#160;You could allocate less by calling&#160;{code}.collect(Collectors.counting());{code}&#160;but since this is a test the current version is fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17009648" author="ifesdjeen" created="Tue, 7 Jan 2020 11:42:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the patch! LGTM, +1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17024773" author="bdeggleston" created="Tue, 28 Jan 2020 00:00:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Comitted to trunk as &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/1f7e3c2835c79363025a01a8470ee85d17457cf8&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;1f7e3c2835c79363025a01a8470ee85d17457cf8&lt;/a&gt;. FailingRepairTest is still failing, but should be addressed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-15508&quot; title=&quot;Failing jvm dtest: FailingRepairTest.testFailingMessage&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-15508&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-15508&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
